====Derived terms====
*എന്റ്റമ്മോ [entamːoː]..........Exclamation, similiar to "Oh my God". Literally "my mother (irregular vocative)".
*[[അമ്മുമ്മ]]..........Grandmother.
*[[വല്ല്യമ്മ]]..........Older maternal aunt. Literally "big mother".
*[[കുഞ്ഞമ്മ]] ''or'' [[കൊച്ചമ്മ]]..........Younger maternal aunt. Literally "small mother".

====Synonyms====

*[[പെറ്റമ്മ]]..........This is used, generally in an affectionate sense or to emphasise motherhood. It literally means "mother who gave birth".

*[[മാതാവ്]]...........This word was derived from Sanskrit ''mātr'' and is considered very formal.
*[[തള്ള]]..........This is a very colloquial and rude term meaning mother.
*[[ഉമ്മ]]..........This is the word that most Muslims who speak malayalam use for mother.
*[[അമ്മച്ചി]].......... This term is used, mainly by Christians, to mean mother. Howevery, it can also be a derogatory term for an old woman.

